body:
As a trivial example, assume this component render code.

``` javascript
render () {
  ...
  return (
    <div>
      <SubComponent />
    </div>
  )
}
```

This helper method

``` javascript
const getSubComponent = componentProps => {
  const component = TestUtils.renderIntoDocument(<Component {...componentProps} />)
  return TestUtils.scryRenderedComponentsWithType(component, SubComponentType)
}
```

makes this test pass,

``` javascript
  it('should initialize a subComponentName with expectedValue', () => {
    const subComponent = getSubComponent(componentProps)
    const expectedValue = value;
    assert.equal(subComponent.props.expectedPropName, expectedValue)
  })
```

while this helper makes it fail (`undefined != expectedValue`)

``` javascript
const getSubComponent = componentProps => {
  const component = TestUtils.renderIntoDocument(<Component {...componentProps} />)
  return TestUtils.scryRenderedDOMComponentsWithClass(component,'sub-component-css-class')
}
```

This does not seem like the expected behavior to me. If it IS expected, then I think it should probably be explicitly mentioned in the docs.
